        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 11:09AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1108 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Pampa, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Codman, Lora, and Miami.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
